The NCCL error "unhandled system error" during
`ncclCommInitRank` in vLLM distributed serving is caused by a missing
`IPC_LOCK` Linux capability or an unmounted `/dev/shm`.
This issue can be resolved by ensuring that the environment has the necessary
permissions and that the shared storage is properly mounted.
